Yep, Heritrix is having trouble getting the robots.txt for the given site.
=
The one successfully completed document that the Frontier report reports is=

the DNS lookup. The other two queued items are the robots.txt and the seed=
.
Testing the robots.txt in a browser leads to a time out as well. 



Wha=
t should happen is that the robots.txt is tried however many times the
Fron=
tier=92s retry policy specifies (and these attempts would be intervals
also=
 specified by the same policy). Once it fails for the last time the seed
wo=
uld be tried. What I THINK happens is that since preconditions are still
no=
t met that the whole robots.txt thing starts all over again. I would need
t=
o do some testing on that. We may want to regard a failure to get the
robot=
s.txt as them being nonexistant... but that may have other
implications.

 =


Anyway adjust the following settings (under the frontier module):



ret=
ry-delay-seconds   -   This is the amount of time that the host queue
will =
be snoozed for before retrying.  Set it to something small.

max-retries  -=
   This is the number of times a URI that encounters a
retryable error (suc=
h as timeout) will be retried. Set it to a smaller value
as well.



This =
should let you test if you can get past robots.txt that always time
out. 

=


- Kris





